The demand for highly customized products at low cost is driving the industry towards Mass Customization. Interactive product conﬁgurators play an essential role in this new trend, and must be able to support more and more complex features. The purpose of this paper is, ﬁrstly, to identify requirements for modern interactive conﬁgurators. Existing modeling and solving technologies for conﬁguration are then reviewed and their limitations dis-cussed. Finally, a proposition for a future product conﬁguration system is described.